This repository contains the design and verification of a ALU implemented in Verilog. The verification environment is built using cocotb, enabling Python-driven simulation and constrained-random testing.

The verification flow includes:

Randomized input stimulus generation
Directed and constrained testing (e.g., ADD-specific sequences)
Automated result checking (self-checking testbench)
Clock-synchronized simulation

This project highlights practical digital design and verification skills, combining hardware description languages with modern software-based verification methodologies.